Package jetbrains.mps.typechecking

Interface TypecheckingQueries

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    LegacyTypecheckingQueries
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultTypecheckingController, SharedSessionTypecheckingController, TypecheckingController, TypecheckingFacade, TypecheckingFacadeComponent.ContextTypecheckingFacade, WorkbenchTypecheckingController
    public interface TypecheckingQueries
    Embodies all queries available to clients of the type checker. This interface is to be implemented by the provider and corresponds to a session participant specific to this provider.

SNode getTypeOf​(SNode expression)

default Collection<SNode> getImmediateSupertypes​(@NotNull

        For users of legacy typesystem, this method functions the same as the now deprecated "immediateSupertypes" expression.

      • coerceType

        @Nullable
SNode coerceType​(SNode type,
                 @NotNull
                 SConcept typeConcept)
        Tries to coerce a type to the form represented with the specified typeConcept. More specifically, the most generic instance of a target type that can be represented with targetConcept is constructed. Then the specified type is converted to that target type, which serves as a pattern. If conversion is possible, the result of the conversion is the coerced type. Returns the coerced type or null, if the type can't be coerced to the specified form. To support the legacy contract, nullable type parameter is accepted, in which case null is returned.

      • coerceType

        @Nullable
SNode coerceType​(SNode type,
                 @NotNull
                 INodeMatchingPattern targetPattern)
        Tries to coerce a type to the form corresponding to the specified targetPattern. This is a more specific variant of the method coerceType(SNode, SConcept), with the difference being that in addition to the target concept one can specify one or more features of the target type. Returns the coerced type or null, if the type can't be coerced to the specified form. To support the legacy contract, nullable type parameter is accepted, in which case null is returned.

      • strongCoerceType

        @Nullable
default SNode strongCoerceType​(SNode type,

                               SConcept typeConcept)
        Provided for compatibility with the legacy system. Is essentially the same as coerceType(SNode, SConcept). To support the legacy contract, nullable type parameter is accepted, in which case null is returned.

      • strongCoerceType

        @Nullable
default SNode strongCoerceType​(SNode type,
                               @NotNull
                               INodeMatchingPattern targetPattern)
        Provided for compatibility with the legacy system. Is essentially the same as coerceType(SNode, INodeMatchingPattern). To support the legacy contract, nullable type parameter is accepted, in which case null is returned.

      • checkRecursively

        void checkRecursively​(SNode root,
                      Consumer<? super NodeReportItem> errorsConsumer)
        Runs typechecking on a node and all its children recursively, collecting the errors reported. The implementation may employ different strategies when deciding whether to run type checking every time or use cached info. Regardless of whether types were checked or not, the {@param errorsConsumer} must receive all errors reported as if root was really checked.

      • clearCache

        void clearCache​(SNode root)
        Clears the internal state (if any) corresponding to the provided root, including collected errors and computed types cache.

      • isCacheUpToDate

        boolean isCacheUpToDate​(SNode root)
        Returns true iff the root doesn't need to be "re-checked", that is all the pending changes to the root have been processed and the cached types and errors are up-to-date. This method only makes sense if the session has been created with "incremental" flag.
